<!-- <h2>Melo-Tea Festival 2025 Darjeeling &ndash; Tea, Music, Culture &amp; Himalayan Magic</h2> -->
<h3>Your Complete Darjeeling Travel &amp; Festival Guide by Wizzride</h3>

<p>The Melo-Tea Festival 2025 is all set to transform Darjeeling into a spectacular valley of music, culture, aroma, and celebrations. Scheduled from 11&ndash;14 December 2025, this four-day Himalayan festival brings together tea heritage, live music, artisan markets, cultural shows, food stalls, and adventure circuits &mdash; making it one of the most anticipated winter festivals in the Eastern Himalayas.</p>
<p>Hosted at Chowrasta &amp; Mall Road, Darjeeling, the festival attracts tea lovers, families, explorers, and music fans from all across India. If you&rsquo;re planning to experience Darjeeling this December, this guide brings you everything &mdash; travel routes, festival highlights, itinerary, best time to visit, and Wizzride cab services.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<hr>
<h2>What is the Melo-Tea Festival 2025?</h2>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p>The festival celebrates the identity and cultural heartbeat of Darjeeling &mdash; Tea, Tunes &amp; Traditions.<br>It is a community-led event supported by local administration and tourism bodies, aiming to promote hill tourism, empower local artists, and revive the cultural spirit of the Darjeeling hills.</p>
<h3>What to Expect at Melo-Tea 2025:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Authentic tea tasting from Darjeeling&rsquo;s finest estates</li>
<li>Rock band competitions (Nepali &amp; Western) with major prize pools</li>
<li>Cultural performances, folk dances, traditional costumes</li>
<li>Local food courts serving momos, thukpa, sel roti &amp; more</li>
<li>Handicraft markets featuring local artists &amp; tea-based products</li>
<li>Adventure circuits (bird watching, village tours, hikes)</li>
<li>Evening concerts and winter carnival vibes</li>
</ul>
<p>It&rsquo;s not just a festival &mdash; it&rsquo;s the true essence of Darjeeling brought to life.</p>
<h2>Festival Highlights &ndash; Why You Shouldn&rsquo;t Miss It</h2>
<h3>&nbsp;1. Tea Tasting Arena</h3>
<p>Learn, sip, and enjoy the world-famous Darjeeling teas &mdash; black, white, green, oolong, and estate specials.</p>
<h3>2. Live Music Performances</h3>
<p>A mix of rock, indie, acoustic, and folk talent performing every evening at Chowrasta.</p>
<h3>&nbsp;3. Band Competitions (Mega Attraction)</h3>
<p>Two large-scale competitions:</p>
<ul>
<li>Nepali Rock Band Contest</li>
<li>Western Rock Band Contest<br>Perfect platform for rising hill artists.</li>
</ul>
<h3>&nbsp;4. Food &amp; Cultural Marketplace</h3>
<p>Explore regional delicacies, handmade crafts, tea souvenirs, and winter special treats.</p>
<h3>&nbsp;5. Marathon &amp; Adventure Events</h3>
<p>Fitness meets culture with hill marathons, mountain circuits, and village exploration trails.</p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<h2>Festival Location &ndash; Chowrasta &amp; Mall Road, Darjeeling</h2>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p>The heart of Darjeeling comes alive during the festival.<br>Chowrasta offers stunning views of the mountains, local life, and picture-perfect backdrops for evening concerts and cultural shows.</p>
<h2>How to Reach Darjeeling for Melo-Tea Festival 2025</h2>
<h3>From Bagdogra Airport (IXB &rarr; Darjeeling)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Distance: 90 km</li>
<li>Travel Time: 3.5&ndash;4 hrs</li>
<li>Best Option: Wizzride Reserved Cab (comfortable &amp; reliable)</li>
</ul>
<h3>From NJP Railway Station (NJP &rarr; Darjeeling)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Distance: 75 km</li>
<li>Travel Time: 3.5&ndash;4.5 hrs</li>
<li>Route: NJP &rarr; Siliguri &rarr; Rohini &rarr; Kurseong &rarr; Ghoom &rarr; Darjeeling</li>
</ul>
<h3>From Siliguri (Siliguri &rarr; Darjeeling)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Distance: 65 km</li>
<li>Travel Time: 3 hrs</li>
</ul>
