<h2>Best Time to Visit Darjeeling in December</h2>
<p>Darjeeling in December offers:</p>
<ul>
<li>Winter chill (2&deg;C&ndash;10&deg;C)</li>
<li>Misty hills &amp; clear mountain skies</li>
<li>Perfect tea-tasting weather</li>
<li>Ideal conditions for festivals &amp; concerts</li>
</ul>
<p>Carry warm layers, gloves, caps, and comfortable shoes.</p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<h2>Top Attractions to Explore During Melo-Tea Festival</h2>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p>While attending the festival, experience Darjeeling&rsquo;s classics:</p>
<h3>1. Tiger Hill Sunrise</h3>
<p>See the golden glow over Kanchenjunga &mdash; a must-experience.</p>
<h3>2. Batasia Loop &amp; War Memorial</h3>
<p>Perfect for panoramic views and toy train photography.</p>
<h3>3. Japanese Peace Pagoda &amp; Buddhist Monastery</h3>
<p>Calming, spiritual, scenic.</p>
<h3>4. Darjeeling Himalayan Railway (Toy Train)</h3>
<p>A UNESCO World Heritage experience through the hills.</p>
<h3>5. Tea Estate Photo Spots</h3>
<p>Capture stunning slopes and learn tea-making from origin to cup.</p>
